  "name": "Black Powder Spectacle",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/skills/weapon_36.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>You can sacrifice ammunition to make a grand spectacle.</em><br /><br /><strong>Prerequisites</strong><br />Amateur Gunslinger or the grit class feature, base attack bonus +4.<br /><br /><strong>Benefits</strong><br />When you spend a swift action to attempt a performance combat check, you can sacrifice one cartridge or an amount of black powder required for a single shot to make either a loud sound or an impressive flash. If you choose to make your weapon's report louder, you gain a +4 bonus on all Intimidate checks you attempt for 1 round. If you choose to create an impressive flash, you gain a +4 bonus on any Perform checks you attempt for 1 round.<br /><strong><br />Combat Trick</strong><br />You can spend 2 stamina points when using Black Powder Spectacle in order to gain a +4 bonus on Intimidate checks and Perform checks for 1 round.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
